TEXT:

#if(v_b3_ch6_air == 0 && v_b3_ch6_tie == 0) {
 "What about Loyrang, then?" Felsig says. "Why don't you send him to execute the criminals while I deal with the ice wall? This traitor hasn't lifted a finger to help in our fight so far, and he was even planning to leave the city before the battle began! He needs to be set straight! He needs to show us that he is still loyal to the king and to the people of Ollendor!"

"If that is what will make you come here faster, then fine!" the captain says. "Loyrang, go execute those criminals."

"Okay, okay," Loyrang says lazily, as he begins walking towards us very slowly. "I'm on it, boss."

"Now Felsig, are you going to come here or not?" the captain says.

"Yeah, I'll be right there," Felsig says, as he now heads towards the captain, walking at a considerably faster pace than Loyrang.

}
#if(v_b3_ch6_air == 0 && v_b3_ch6_tie == 0 || v_b3_ch6_air == 0 && v_b3_ch6_tie == 1) {
 Right after the captain stops talking, Daren is slammed into the ground by an invisible force, like the rest of us. For a moment, I see Daren's sword budging a few inches as he tries to make it fly back into his hand, but the pain in his wrist is clearly preventing him from focusing properly. 

The captain does not notice what Daren is trying to do, and instead he directs his attention towards Gontrok, who is still fighting Hadrik.

"Gontrok!" the captain shouts. "Come here and help me destroy this ice wall behind me! The ambassador is trapped and can't get to safety!"

"I'm a little busy here, captain," Gontrok says, as he blocks Hadrik's fist with his right hand and then crouches to avoid a kick to his face.

"Damn it..." the captain says, and now he turns his gaze towards the air elementalist elf. "Hey, Felsig! Get over here and cut a hole through this wall with your wind magic! And don't try to execute the criminals while you're on your way here. That's an order!"

"What?..." the elf says. "Why would you want them alive?"

"I don't," the captain says, "but with the amount of tricks they've pulled out of their sleeves so far, I wouldn't be surprised if they were to make use of your own wind blades to free themselves or even kill you. I'm not taking that risk. The ambassador's safety remains our highest priority."

}
#if(v_b3_ch6_air == 0 && v_b3_ch6_tie == 1) {
 "Fine, I'll be right there," Felsig says, and then he begins heading towards the captain.

}
#if(v_b3_ch6_tie == 0 && v_b3_ch6_air >= 1) {
 "Of course he can't hear me..." the captain says. "Loyrang, can you-- no, never mind, your swords aren't sharp enough to cut through this wall... Ambassador, I'm afraid that you're going to have to go through the main street and then take that alleyway over there in order to return to your shelter. Do you understand?"

"You're telling me to get even closer to those murderers while you're not there to protect me?!" the ambassador says. "What if they kill me?"

"They're not going to kill you," the captain says. "They are all being immobilized, and I will make a small mobile barrier between you and them to protect you as you walk, just in case. Now please go to your shelter. Even I can't hold them like this forever."

"I will go," the ambassador says, "but if anything happens to me, you will pay with your life! Mark my words!"

"Duly noted," the captain says, as the ambassador is now heading into the street we are in, so he can reach his shelter.

}
#if(v_b3_ch6_air == 0 && v_b3_ch6_tie == 0 || v_b3_ch6_air == 0 && v_b3_ch6_tie == 1 || v_b3_ch6_tie == 0 && v_b3_ch6_air >= 1 || v_b3_ch6_tie == 1 && v_b3_ch6_air >= 1) {
 Even under these conditions, Daren still somehow manages to cancel the invisible force by moving his sword very slightly to the right, and then he quickly gets up, making a rush for the captain, while all of the boulders and the rubble around us that had been magically created are now slowly fading into thin air.

The captain of the guards puts both his hands in front of him and uses his aura manipulation technique to push Daren away, while he uses the pressure from before to immobilize the rest of us again. The next thing that the captain tries to do is pull Daren's sword away from him, but he ends up pulling on his whole arm along with the sword, because the weapon simply won't detach itself from the palm of his hand.

"You are using... aura manipulation to glue your sword to your hand?" the captain asks Daren, somewhat surprised. "It looks like you've learned a few tricks since the last time I saw you. However--"

Daren's wrist suddenly begins to twist in a very unnatural way, as he struggles to suppress a scream of pain. After a few seconds, the sword finally unglues itself from his palm and flies into the hands of the guard captain.

"--anyone can clearly see that you are still a novice at aura manipulation," the captain continues, as he throws Daren's sword away while looking at him in disgust. "A small twist of the wrist is all that it takes to break your concentration at your current level. Now lay down on the ground, where you and your kind belong."

}
#if(v_b3_ch6_tie == 0 && v_b3_ch6_air >= 1 || v_b3_ch6_tie == 1 && v_b3_ch6_air >= 1) {
 Right after the captain stops talking, Daren is slammed into the ground by an invisible force, like the rest of us. For a moment, I see Daren's sword budging a few inches as he tries to make it fly back into his hand, but the pain in his wrist is clearly preventing him from focusing properly. 

The captain does not notice what Daren is trying to do, and instead he directs his attention towards Gontrok, who is still fighting Hadrik.

"Gontrok!" the captain shouts. "Come here and help me destroy this ice wall behind me! The ambassador is trapped and can't get to safety!"

"I'm a little busy here, captain," Gontrok says, as he blocks Hadrik's fist with his right hand and then crouches to avoid a kick to his face.

"Damn it..." the captain says, and now he turns his gaze towards the sky, shouting loudly in the hopes that his voice will reach the earth elementalist. "Bolwick, can you hear me?!"

He waits for a few seconds, but he gets no answer.

}
#if(v_b3_ch6_tie == 1 && v_b3_ch6_air >= 1) {
