"Why are you so surprised?" Daren says. "No matter how fast you spin it, an element is still an element. As long as the tornado is small enough, I can still absorb it. Here, you can have it back."

 He then swings his sword in the elf's direction, as the small tornado gets flung away from the blade and straight for the air elementalist, getting bigger and bigger until it reaches its original size.

"Aah!" the elf screams. "Get away from me!"

As he runs away, the tornado keeps following him, and now the captain who was forced to move out of the whirlwind's way is finding himself in a bit of a bind, because Daren has taken advantage of this distraction to close in on him fast. Before he gets to react, Daren sticks his sword through his heart, killing the man almost immediately. The captain soon falls to the ground in a puddle of his own blood, as Daren calmly sheathes his sword and turns back to look at us.

