"I didn't," Rose says. "I actually called Barry a little earlier, because I wanted to tell him that I could probably still use my time-freezing power once more for the day in case you guys needed it. But before I got the chance to say anything, I realized from the noises that you were all in the middle of a battle, so I decided that I should just wait for the right opportunity to help, instead of calling out to you and making you lose your focus."

"Well, your intervention couldn't have been timed any better," Daren says. "We may well have all died without your help."

"Your friend on the transceiver..." Kelrim says. "She froze the time? Is that why you were able to cancel the captain's aura technique all of a sudden?"

"Oh, that's right, you were also frozen by Rose's spell so you couldn't tell what was happening," Daren says. "Yes, Rose froze the time for a while, and that gave me the opportunity to-- Kelrim, are you alright?... Your face looks really pale! I mean... at least I think it's pale. It's not normal for it to be such a light shade of green, is it?"

"Oh, I'm fine..." Kelrim says. "It's just... it's just that... if your friend hadn't intervened, I would have most likely cast that nausea spell that I told you about before on the captain. I may have been only seconds away from ending my own life, and the thought of that terrifies me a little."

}
