ID: B3-Ch06b-Carry
TEXT:

#if(v_b3_ch6_kelrim != 1 && v_b3_ch6_plan != 3) {
 "Guys, I suggest that we run as far away from here as our legs can carry us," I say.

"Why?" Daren asks me. "Do you think something's going to happen with that drone?"

"I don't know, but I don't want to wait and find out," I say. "Make a barrier behind us as we run too, just to be sure."

"Well, you're the Overseer expert..." Daren says. "Alright, you heard him everyone! Run away quick, and leave the defense to me!"

We all sprint away from the drone, with Daren making sure to be the last one in the group so that he can hold a protective barrier between us and the metal ball with his shield. When he reaches Kelrim's dead body, Daren picks it up from the ground and puts it on his right shoulder, while he continues to run. As we are distancing ourselves from the drone, we suddenly hear it beeping three times and then it self-destructs, generating an explosion so big that it almost reaches the buildings on the side of the street and creating a wide crater in the ground.

}
