}
 Even with the distance we've put between us and the drone, the impact of the blast still managed to reach us but we were already pretty far from the center of the explosion so it was nothing that Darenâ€™s barrier couldnâ€™t handle. As we now stop to look at the singeing hot earth forming the crater behind us and at all the windows that were broken by the explosionâ€™s shockwave, I immediately turn my eyes towards the drones in the sky that are still floating innocently, as if they were completely unaware of what's happening below.

"I guess you're not our Overseer expert for nothing," Daren says, as he is still looking at the scorched earth from the area we left. "If we were any closer to that explosion, things could have ended pretty badly."

"I don't think it's over yet," I tell him, as I'm still looking attentively at the sky. "The Overseer seems to have finally found a way to attack us despite his self-imposed 'maintenance mode'. He's not going to stop until he runs out of drones that he can drop on us. Illuna, could you cool down that hot crater a little?"

"Will do," she says, and then she sends a small torrent of water to flood the hole in the ground that has formed from the explosion.

 When the water comes in contact with the flaming hot rocks, a good deal of it evaporates from the heat, but this helps to lower the temperature of the ground enough for us to be able to walk on it again. Once the earth is all cooled down, Illuna dismisses the leftover water, and then she looks at me.

"The ground has been cooled," Illuna tells me.

