"Choosing to run away from the metal ball was a surprisingly good decision, coming from someone like you," Albert says, as I now see him coming out of invisibility. "Maybe it wasn't a coincidence that you survived in the mage tournament for so long."

"I'm guessing that the first thing you did when you saw the drone falling from the sky was to turn invisible and to get as far away from it as possible, then?" I say.

"Obviously," Albert says.

"I'll call Barry to teleport us out of here before anything else happens," Daren says, as he takes out his transceiver again.

}
