"He... sacrificed himself for our sake, and for the people in the quarantine area," Daren says, in a sad tone. "We would not have made it out of there alive if not for him. We are all in his debt..."

"I see," the teleporter guy says, as he looks away, towards the ground.

"I will take Kelrim back to the waiting room," Albert says, as he approaches Daren. "There are many people that would like to say their goodbyes to him, especially in the quarantine area."

"...Make sure that he gets a proper burial," Daren says, as he hands Kelrim's body to Albert somewhat hesitantly.

"We will do what we can," Albert says, and then he takes the goblin in his arms. "Now if you'll please excuse me, I need to go report the death of the captain of the guards to our king. I'm certain that he will be both relieved and saddened by the news, considering their long history together. I'll be seeing you later."

